@page "/hero"
<PageTitle>Hero - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="hero">Hero</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The Hero component creates a large, prominent banner section — ideal for
                landing pages and key call-to-action areas.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>&lt;Hero&gt;
    &lt;H1&gt;Build faster with Saascade&lt;/H1&gt;
    &lt;P&gt;Design-system-agnostic Blazor components.&lt;/P&gt;
    &lt;Button&gt;Get Started&lt;/Button&gt;
&lt;/Hero&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="parameters">Parameters</h2>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Class</td><td>string?</td><td>Additional CSS classes.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Style</td><td>string?</td><td>Inline styles.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>ChildContent</td><td>RenderFragment</td><td>Hero content.</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="hero-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Hero</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Hero</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Bootstrap 5, the Hero component is styled as a jumbotron-style section.
                Bootstrap 5 removed the jumbotron component in favor of utility classes, so
                the Saascade Bootstrap 5 design system composes the hero from container,
                padding, and background utilities. You can adjust the hero's height, background
                color, and text alignment through the Specialization or Class parameters.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="hero-daisyui">DaisyUI Hero</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Hero</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In DaisyUI, the Hero component maps to the DaisyUI hero class. DaisyUI's hero
                component centers its content both vertically and horizontally by default and
                supports a hero-content child for the text and action area. The hero adapts its
                background and text styling to the active DaisyUI theme without requiring
                additional class configuration.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="hero-basecoat">Basecoat Hero</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Hero</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Basecoat, the Hero component is composed from Tailwind utility classes that
                create a full-width centered section. The default composition includes flex
                layout, vertical padding, and text centering utilities. You can control the
                hero's background, minimum height, and content alignment by passing additional
                Tailwind utilities through the Class or Specialization parameters.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("hero", "Hero"),
    new TocItem("overview", "Overview", 2),
    new TocItem("parameters", "Parameters", 2),
    new TocItem("hero-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5 Hero", 2),
    new TocItem("hero-daisyui", "DaisyUI Hero", 2),
    new TocItem("hero-basecoat", "Basecoat Hero", 2)
])" />

</div>
